# No secrets belong here. Any VITE_-prefixed variable is inlined into the
# client bundle and becomes publicly visible, so the Groq API key must only
# ever live in server/.env — the Vite dev proxy (see vite.config.js) routes
# /api/* requests to the backend, so the client doesn't need to know its URL.

# Supabase project URL and ANON key — these two ARE safe to expose publicly.
# The anon key only grants what Row Level Security policies allow; it is
# not a secret like GROQ_API_KEY or the Supabase service role key, both of
# which must stay server-only. Get both from Project Settings > API.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
